        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 6 at 3:27PM EDT until September 6 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Gray ME</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Hillsborough to near Fitzwilliam, moving east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Antrim, Marlborough, Rindge, Windsor, Dublin, Hancock, Jaffrey,
Warner, Hillsborough, Bennington, Nelson, Fitzwilliam, Harrisville,
Troy, Richmond, Bradford, Peterborough, Sharon, Henniker, and
Deering.

This also includes...
Mount Monadnock.

This includes Interstate 89 near mile marker 20.
</description>
        <instruction>A tornado watch remains in effect for the warned area. Tornadoes can
develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Although a tornado is not
immediately likely, if one is spotted act quickly and move to a place
of safety inside a sturdy structure, such as a basement or small
interior room.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
